
---


@startuml
skinparam noteStyle rectangle

' Entities
class Center {
  +name: String (unique)
  +address: String
  +rooms: Set(Room)
}

class Room {
  +number: int (unique within center)
  +maxCapacity: int
  +center: Center
}

class Person {
  +firstName: String
  +lastName: String
  +birthDate: Date
  +sessions: Set(Session)
}

class Trainer extends Person {
  +diploma: String
}

class Session {
  +date: Date
  +startTime: Time
  +room: Room
  +type: String (optional)
  +participants: Set(Person)
  +supervisor: Trainer (optional)
}

' Relationships
Center "1" -- "0..*" Room : has
Room "1" -- "1" Center : belongs to
Person "1" -- "0..*" Session : participates in
Trainer "1" -- "0..*" Session : supervises (group session only)
Session "1" -- "0..*" Person : participant
Session "1" -- "0..1" Trainer : supervisor (only for group sessions)

note right of Center
  Each center has multiple rooms.
  Rooms are uniquely numbered.
  Address is atomic.
end note

note left of Person
  Unique combination of first name,
  last name, and birth date.
end note

note left of Trainer
  In addition to Person attributes,
  a trainer has a diploma.
end note

note right of Session
  Sessions can be individual or group.
  Group sessions have a supervisor (trainer).
  All sessions must be in a room.
end note

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Points:

- **Center**: Represents a fitness center with a unique name, address, and multiple rooms.
- **Room**: Has a number (unique per center), max capacity, and is associated with one center.
- **Person**: Base class for all individuals. Includes first name, last name, and birth date.
- **Trainer**: Subclass of `Person` with an additional `diploma` attribute.
- **Session**: Contains date, start time, room, and type (for group sessions). Can have participants and a supervisor (only for group sessions).

This model supports tracking:
- Members who participate in sessions.
- Trainers who supervise group sessions.
- Prospects and interns who haven't participated or supervised yet.
- Sessions that occur at the same time but in different rooms/centers.

